blic? If my file name for Reload4jTest is public but not active, I could broaden the scope. I need to check if resources like native-image reflect config are needed to make JmDNS methods accessible and ensure everything runs correctly under native conditions.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering native test configurations**\\n\\nIn the native test setup, I think it likely uses agent output along with repository metadata. However, the native-image build may need JmDNS reachability metadata generated as well. I don't plan to alter the current configurations. I'm noticing a potential issue with `jmDNSClass.getMethod(\\\"create\\\", null)` in Java 17 since passing a null parameterTypes array might throw a NullPointerException. I wonder if I need to use `Objects.requireNonNull(parameterTypes)` to avoid that.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_C056K5UNL4Rr8rzrq0vyyVy9|fc_0ee99c174a0fb3150169efd390922481a0a1c68bcd50dfbb9a", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ch.qos.reload4j/reload4j/1.2.19/src/test/java/ch_qos_reload4j/reload4j/ZeroConfSupportTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage ch_qos_reload4j.reload4j;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.util.LinkedHashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport java.util.UUID;\n\nimport javax.jmdns.JmDNS;\n\nimport org.apache.log4j.net.ZeroConfSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.AfterAll;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class ZeroConfSupportTest {\n    private static final String SERVICE_TYPE = \"_reload4j-test._tcp.local.\";\n\n    @AfterAll\n    public static void closeSharedJmDns() throws IOException {\n        Object jmDns = ZeroConfSupport.getJMDNSInstance();\n        if (jmDns instanceof JmDNS) {\n            ((JmDNS) jmDns).close();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void shouldAdvertiseAndUnadvertiseServiceWithJmDns() {\n        Map<String, String> properties = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n        properties.put(\"library\", \"reload4j\");\n        properties.put(\"scenario\", \"zero-conf-support\");\n\n        ZeroConfSupport support = new ZeroConfSupport(SERVICE_TYPE, 12345, uniqueServiceName(), properties);\n\n        assertThat(ZeroConfSupport.getJMDNSInstance()).isInstanceOf(JmDNS.class);\n        support.advertise();\n        support.unadvertise();\n    }\n\n    private static String uniqueServiceName() {\n        return \"reload4j-\" + UUID.randomUUID();\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 455, "output": 2184, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24655, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777324920911, "responseId": "resp_0ee99c174a0fb3150169efd379556481a0bc1533284cd5b84c"}}
